      "comment_id" : 28000644,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "+1 for a complete code example. One additional note here is that hashing isn&#39;t guaranteed to be the same from run to run. That means that the list printed after &#39;Set values .....&#39; might be &#39;ABC&#39; one run and &#39;CBA&#39; another run. As I mentioned in my answer, you could use a tree set to get a stable ordering. Another option would be to use a LinkedHashSet which remembers the order that items were added to it."
    } ],
