    "question_id" : 1429860,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Java 1.8, the stream API can be used to convert a list to set. For example, the code below shows the conversion of a list to a set:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>List&lt;String&gt; empList = Arrays.asList(&quot;java&quot;, &quot;python&quot;, &quot;.net&quot;, &quot;javaScript&quot;, &quot;php&quot;);\nSet&lt;String&gt; set = empList.stream().collect(Collectors.toSet());\nset.forEach(value -&gt; System.out.printf(&quot;%s &quot;, value));\n</code></pre>\n<p>In case the list contains objects and I want to create a set out of it:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>List&lt;Employee&gt; empList = Arrays.asList(new Employee(1, 1000, &quot;Chandra Shekhar&quot;, 6000),\nnew Employee(2, 1000, &quot;Rajesh&quot;, 8000), new Employee(3, 1004, &quot;Rahul&quot;, 9000),\nnew Employee(4, 1001, &quot;Suresh&quot;, 12000), new Employee(5, 1004, &quot;Satosh&quot;, 7000));\n\nSet&lt;String&gt; set = empList.stream().map(emp -&gt; emp.getName()).collect(Collectors.toSet());\nSystem.out.println(set);        \n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
